  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Vulnerable families have access to dignified basic Integrated services in IDPs and host communities in Daynile, Kahda and Dharkinley district in Banadir region.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is aimed at supporting the most vulnerable persons in Mogadishu particularly in the Kahda, Daynile and Dharkinley districts with CCCM and Shelter/NFI interventions while SOYDA will be implementing protection and wash activities. . Owing to high needs of the displaced persons SSWC will enhance proper camp management and coordination this an integral part of the intervention due to the improper living conditions in the camps to overcome the project will further improve the settlements by providing NFIs materials for helping the less fortunate to have decent housing and other useful material for shelter. Despite the poor settlement the people living in the camps are prone to protection related incidents, its therefore prudent to enhance the lives of the people particularly women and girls whose rights are violated.  The settlements in the camps are congested and services offered mismatch the population that lives in the camps, this therefore leads to health hazards.  The project will cover coordination of camps through establishing structures and maintaining the sites through supporting the community with conditional cash for work activities. Under Shelter/NFI SSWC will distribute portable solar lamps and NFI and conduct post distribution monitoring after distribution.</narrative>
  </description>
